body:
In [this reddit discussion](https://www.reddit.com/r/golang/comments/3jlr82/test_coverage/cuqnvdz?context=4), /u/jerf has a nice suggestion: label lines that should be impossible to reach to improve coverage. Something like follows:

    res, err := prudentFunction("constant")
    if err != nil {
      panic(fmt.Sprintf("The impossible has happened: %v", err)) // gocover: Ignore
    }

The coverage tool could then instrument the line and ignore it if there are 0 passes, and issue an error if there were more than zero.
